<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mitterrand's Doctor Sentenced to 4 Months in Jail </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Doctor Claude Gubler, personal doctor
of the late president Francois Mitterrand and author of the book
"The Great Secret," was given four months in jail in suspense
today for violating professional ethics of maintaining secrets.
</P>
<P>
The 17th Chamber of the Correctional Tribunal of Paris today
also announced a fine of 30,000 francs (6,000 U.S. dollars) on
Michel Gonod, Gubler's co-author, and a fine of 60,000 francs
(12,000 dollars) on Olivier Orban, their publisher.
</P>
<P>
"This is another time when the lie of the state has won. This
decision weakens the trade I am doing," said Orban after the
court, presided over by Judge Jean-Yves Monfort, made the
decisions.
</P>
<P>
Gubler himself did not attend today's court session, and the
attorneys defending the three accused have indicated that they
might make appeals.
</P>
<P>
The court said that Gubler was guilty of violating his code of
ethics for maintaining the secret of a confidant, revealing secret
information on the disease, symptoms, medical examinations and
their outcomes, reactions of Mitterrand and surgery interventions,
and having the consciousness of committing a fraudulent action.
</P>
<P>
But the court also said that Gubler wrote the book not out of
"detestable intentions such as making money" but out of a feeling
of confusion as a wounded man would have when he was abandoned in
the field by a friend after a "passionately lived relationship."
</P>
<P>
The court did not specify whether a sick statesman and a common
patient have the same right to maintain secret about their health
situation, and only each patient has the same right to maintain
their medical records secret.
</P>
<P>
Gubler was sued by Danielle Mitterrand, the widow of Francois
Mitterrand, after he published "The Great Secret" soon after the
death of Mitterrand in January this year.
</P>
<P>
Mitterrand had suffered from gland cancer for many years before
he died of the disease. His disease was never officially revealed
until his death. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
