<HEADLINE> Top World Bank Official Advocates Regional Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The Southern African Development
Community (SADC) countries should find a way of working together
constructively to ensure and enhance trade in the region, a
visiting senior World Bank official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters after his 40-minute talks with
Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe in Harare, World Bank
Vice-president for Africa Callisto Madavo said southern Africa
could be the locomotive to pull the rest of Africa in terms of
trade and development.
</P>
<P>
"Africa faces great development challenges but in these
challenges lie opportunities which Zimbabwe and other southern
African countries could exploit in terms of trade if they can
work together," said the Zimbabwean-born Madavo, who is on a
six-day tour of the country.
</P>
<P>
Madavo said he had briefed Mugabe on his development
discussions with cabinet ministers and his visit to rural areas
as well as the World Bank's programmes of support to Zimbabwe.
</P>
</TEXT>
