<HEADLINE> Indian Government Reshuffled Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The month-long Indian government
today witnessed a second expansion in less than a week as Prime
Minister Deve Gowda inducted four new ministers of state into his
council of ministers.
</P>
<P>
Among the four new ministers is Raghuvans Prasad Singh of the
Janata Dal from Bihar, who had earlier sulked about his status as
minister of state, but took oath today as minister of state with
independent charge.
</P>
<P>
The other three are Satpalji Maharaj of all India Indira
Congress from Uttar Pradesh, and N.V.N. Somu and T.R. Balu of
Dravida Munnetra Kazhagam (DMK, a regional party in Tamil Nadu)
from Tamil Nadu.
</P>
<P>
Gowda also elevated Textiles Minister R.L. Jalappa and
Communications Minister Beni Prasad Verma to the cabinet rank.
Verma could not take oath today as he was away in Bangalore,
Karnataka.
</P>
<P>
The portfolios of the new ministers will be announced later.
</P>
<P>
With today's induction, the strength of the council of
ministers goes up to 39, including the prime minister.
</P>
<P>
Of them, apart from the prime minister, 18 are cabinet
ministers, 10 ministers of state with independent charge and 10
others ministers of state.  
</P>
</TEXT>
