<HEADLINE> CIS Leaders Congratulate Yeltsin on Poll Victory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Leaders of the Commonwealth of
Independent States (CIS) have congratulated Russian President
Boris Yeltsin for winning the presidential election.
</P>
<P>
Ukrainian President Leonid Kuchma sent a congratulatory
telegram to Yeltsin Thursday, in which he said that Yeltsin's
victory is a significant contribution to consolidating
international security.
</P>
<P>
Alexandr Lukashenko, president of Belarus, predicted that the
course of integration among CIS countries will be promoted
following Yeltsin's success.
</P>
<P>
Nursultan Nazarbayev, president of Kazakhstan, believed that
Yeltsin would maintain his support for CIS integration and that
relations between Kazakhstan and Russia will be boosted on
the basis of friendship, equality and independence.
</P>
<P>
Armenian President Levon Ter-Petrosyan in a congratulatory
message called Yeltsin's victory a truly great historical event.
</P>
<P>
Georgian President Eduard Shevardnadze said Yeltsin's
re-election will influence events in Georgia and the entire
Transcaucasia region, bringing peace to areas of conflict.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin is poised take on his second term as Russian president after
winning Wednesday's second round presidential election.
</P>
<P>
With nearly 54 percent of the vote, he beat his political rival
Gennady Zyuganov by about 13 percentage points with almost all the
votes counted.
</P>
<P>
The two men entered the run-off after beating eight other
candidates but failing to win more than 50 percent of the votes in
the first round on June 16. 
</P>
</TEXT>
