<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World's Five Most Expensive Cities are in Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Five of the world's 10 most
expensive cities are in Asia, an international survey on the cost
of living shows.
</P>
<P>
The five most expensive cities in the world are Tokyo, Osaka,
Beijing, Shanghai and Hong Kong, with Seoul and Singapore ranked
seventh and 10th, according to the survey of 139 cities around the
world by the Geneva-based company Corporate Resources Group (CRG).
</P>
<P>
The only European cities to rank among the top ten are Moscow
in sixth place, followed by the Swiss cities of Geneva and Zurich
taking eighth and ninth place. Europe's least expensive cities are
Vilnius in Lithuania, Limassol in Cyprus and Birmingham, England.
</P>
<P>
The report also included a separate ranking of hotel and
related travel costs. It shows that Hong Kong is the most
expensive city for business travellers, followed by Moscow, Tokyo,
Brussels and Geneva.
</P>
<P>
The dominance of Asian cities in the top ten is partly due to
the high cost of housing which is included for the first time in
the ranking's index, says the report.
</P>
<P>
Housing costs in Beijing are now the most expensive in the
world, followed by Tokyo and Hong Kong. The only non-Asian city to
rank among the top ten for housing is Moscow which has also seen
dramatic increases in prices for good accommodation.
</P>
<P>
The CRG cost of living index is intended for use by governments
and international firms to protect the purchasing power of
personnel sent abroad.
</P>
<P>
The study is based on a basket of over 200 products which
includes food consumed at home, alcohol, tobacco, domestic
supplies and services, home services, personal care, clothing and
footwear, utilities, transport, sport and leisure, home
entertainment, housing, schooling and travel.
</P>
<P>
In the western hemisphere, Sao Paulo in Brazil has become the
most expensive city, followed by Buenos Aires, Argentia, and Rio
de Janeiro, Brazil. The American and Canadian cities compare very
favorably to many European and Asian cities. Mexico City and
Monterrey in Mexico remain among the least expensive cities in the
world.
</P>
<P>
The most expensive cities in Africa are Libreville in Gabon and
Brazzaville in the Congo, taking 31st and 32nd place in the list.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
