<HEADLINE> Education Is the Key to Shaking Off Poverty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Education and scientific knowledge
are vital for the elimination of poverty, and people in the less
developed areas should place priority on learning new skills,
Vice-Premier Li Lanqing said during a tour of north China's Shanxi
Province.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier said that providing farmers with proper
education will help enhance their abilities, which in turn will
promote social development in rural areas.
</P>
<P>
