<HEADLINE> Dalian Creates New Life Insurance Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, July 5 (Xinhua) -- A new life insurance policy has been
created in Dalian for local police officers or residents injured
or killed while safeguarding public security.
</P>
<P>
The Dalian branch of the China People's Insurance Company,
signed an agreement today with Dalian Social Public Security Funds
to provide insurance benefits for people injured or killed while
combatting crime.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, the insurance company will pay
30,000 yuan (about 3,500 US dollars) to the beneficiaries of those
killed; 20,000 yuan for people who are badly injured; 10,000 yuan
for those who receive light injuries.
</P>
<P>
The company will also provide up to 8,000 yuan for additional
medical treatment.
</P>
