<HEADLINE> Over 70,000 Criminal Cases Registered in Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Over 70,000 criminal cases
were registered in Ethiopia from July to December last year with
the number of detained alleged culprits reaching 112,983, a
police report quoted by the official Ethiopian News Agency said
today.
</P>
<P>
The report issued by the Research Centre of the Central Bureau
of the Police Force said the major crimes committed include
theft, thuggery and murder.
</P>
<P>
The report said the average crime rate is 15 to 16 per hour.
</P>
<P>
It said, there were about 10,964 women culprits, with 50
percent of the detainees aged between 19 and 30.
</P>
<P>
More than half of the crimes took place in the rural areas and
the illiterate comprised the bulk of the criminals, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
The report added that the criminal cases registered in Addis
Ababa, Oromiya and Amhara regions accounted for 71 percent of the
total. enditem

