<HEADLINE> Central-Eastern European Economic Summit to Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The first Central and Eastern
European Economic Summit organized by the Geneva-based World
Economic Forum will open Sunday in Salzburg, Austria, organizers
said today.
</P>
<P>
Heads of state and high-ranking government officials from 13
countries in the region and their neighbors, including Austria,
Germany and Russia, as well as several hundred international
business leaders will attend the three-day summit.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will officially open Sunday evening with a plenary
session titled "Central and Eastern Europe: on the brink of a new
era." Presidents from Albania, Romania, the Slovak Republic,
Ukraine and Bulgaria as well as prime ministers of Poland,
Hungary, Yugoslavia and Latvia will be present.
</P>
<P>
Over the three days, the participants will discuss ways to
sustain economic growth and competitive advantage in the region.
Regional security problems such as NATO expansion as well as
integration of Eastern and Central European countries into the
European Union will also be on the agenda, according to the forum.
</P>
</TEXT>
