<HEADLINE> Australian Foreign Minister Visits Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Australian Foreign Minister
Alexander Downer and his Vietnamese counterpart Nguyen Manh Cam
today held talks on promoting bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Australia currently ranks eighth among foreign investors in
Vietnam with an investment of 870 million U.S. dollars in 58
projects and both sides welcomed the steady expansion of bilateral
ties especially in trade and investment.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers exchanged views on a wide range of bilateral
and international issues of mutual interest and agreed to continue
to work together on international and regional affairs.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam welcomed Australia's "important and increasingly close"
ties with the (Southeast Asia) region and the countries of the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) in particular, a
press release on the meeting said.
</P>
<P>
Australia welcomed Vietnam's continuing efforts at integration
in the region and the world through its membership of ASEAN, the
normalization of relations with the United States and the European
Community and its desire to join the Asia-Pacific Economic
Cooperation (APEC), the release said.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also agreed to work with other regional neighbors
to develop the Mekong Basin region through the Mekong River
Commission, the Mekong Development Cooperation and the Indo-China
Development Forum. 
</P>
