<HEADLINE> Cyprus, Italian Airlines Agree on Joint Flights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus Airways, the island's
national carrier, has reached an agreement with Italy's Alitalia
airlines on joint flights to and from Rome and Larnaca during the
winter period, it was announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The announcement said that the two companies agreed, after
lengthy negotiations, to use joint flight code numbers as of the
end of October this year.
</P>
<P>
The agreement envisages that Cyprus Airways and Alitalia each
perform one weekly flight to and from Larnaca and Rome and offer
seats to their respective passengers, giving them more frequent
flights and better service.
</P>
<P>
Negotiations between the two airlines are continuing with a
view to extending the agreement beyond the winter period, the
announcement said.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus Airways considers this agreement as another step in
their policy for joint ventures and co-operation with other
airlines. 
</P>
</TEXT>
