<HEADLINE> French Woman Raped in Cambodian Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 6 (Xinhua) -- A French woman was raped Friday
evening in a hotel in the Cambodian capital, and her three
companions were robbed, said Agence France Presse today quoting
French Embassy in Phnom Penh.
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old French woman, whose name was not revealed, was
raped by an unidentified Cambodian man. Police said they had not
found the assaulter yet.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time in two years for foreigners to be
assaulted in Cambodia, according to foreign humanitarian groups in
Phnom Penh.
</P>
<P>
Cambodian King Norodom Sihanouk said on Friday that the
Cambodian government can no longer guarantee foreigners of their
security. 
</P>
