<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Foreign Minister Abdus
Samad Azad today emphasized the need for economic diplomacy,
saying that the government's foreign policy objective will be best
served through efforts to promote trade and economic relations
with other countries.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the official news agency BSS, the minister
said in the present day context economic diplomacy was needed to
develop the country's economy by expanding external trade, finding
overseas markets for Bangladeshi products and creating employment
opportunities.
</P>
<P>
Priority would be given to resolving all outstanding problems
with neighbors including India, he said, stressing the need to
arrive at a solution of the long standing water sharing problem
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister confirmed that the new Indian government
had sent messages of goodwill to the Bangladeshi government and
India has shown interest in resolving problems with Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
He said that both sides should make renewed efforts to meet
frequently and discuss all bilateral issues.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister also stressed the need of strengthening
further economic cooperation among the members of the South Asian
Association for Regional Cooperation.  
</P>
