<HEADLINE> Criville Grabs Pole Position </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Alex Criville of Spain edged out his
 Honda teammate Michael Doohan of Australia on Saturday and
grabbed pole position for the 500cc race at Sunday's German Grand
Prix in Nurburgring, Germany.
</P>
<P>
Criville covered the 4.542 kilometers (2.83 miles) Nurburgring
circuit in one minute 40.347 seconds while two-time word champion
Doohan was only fractionally slower in 1:40.386.
</P>
<P>
American Scott Russsell was third-quickest in qualifying on a
Suzuki, ahead of Italian Doriano Romboni on an Aprilia.
</P>
<P>
The qualifying was effectively cut short by rain mid-way
through the hour-long session, just as Doohan was preparing to
mount his assault.
</P>
<P>
Doohan holds an emphatic lead going into Sunday's race, the
eighth round of the world championship.
</P>
<P>
The Australian has 146 points to Criville's 93 and the 83 of
Spaniard Alex Barros and will be bidding for his fifth straight
victory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
