<HEADLINE> Ethiopia to send 35 Athletes to Atlanta Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Olympic Committee
announced here on Sunday that a total of 35 athletes will be sent
to compete in the coming Atlanta Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to local media, President of the Ethiopian Olympic
Committee Yami Kebede said the Ethiopian contingent will leave
for Atlanta on July 15 or 16.
</P>
<P>
A total of 35 athletes will compete in the 800m, 1,500m, 5,000,
and 10,000m track events as well as in the marathon and boxing.
</P>
<P>
Yami said world record holder Haile Gebreselassie will take
part in the men's 5,000m and 10,000m races while Barcelona gold
medalist Derartu Tulu will run in the women's 10,000 meters. They
are the gold medal hopefuls of the country.
</P>
<P>
He added that Ethiopian athletes are expected to put up good
performance at the Olympics because they had trained very hard in
the intensive preparations for the Games.  
