<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Introduces Styrene Device from Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The Jilin Chemical Industry Stock
Co. Ltd. in northeast China will introduce a Japanese-made styrene
device to be used in the construction of a 100,000-ton styrene
project.
</P>
<P>
The device, made by Mitsubishi Heavy Industries, Ltd. of Japan,
is a supporting item for the 300,000-ton ethylene project of the
Jilin Chemical Industry Stock Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
Styrene is a major synthetic material monomer that is widely
used in agriculture, medicine, as a coating material, and for
accessory ingredients.
</P>
<P>
The project involves an investment of 750 million yuan (about
90 million US dollars), and will be put into production in 1998,
</P>
<P>
By using the existing facilities of the Organic Synthesis
Factory that are operated by the Jilin Chemical Industry Stock
Co. Ltd., the project can adopt production technology provided
by ABB Lummus Global Inc. of the United States.
</P>
<P>
Jiao Haikun, general manager of the Jilin Chemical Industry
Stock Co. Ltd., said at today's contract signing ceremony that the
existing styrene device at the organic synthesis factory has been
in operation for 13 years, and needs to be replaced with an
advanced model.
</P>
<P>
The general manager said that China has long lagged behind in
styrene production and imports a large amount each year to meet
the domestic demand.
</P>
<P>
By the year 2000, China will need 1.2 million tons of styrene;
the current national production capacity is only 280,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
Should all the styrene production devices under construction be
put into use, production capacity could only reach 700,000 tons,
he said. 
</P>
