<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi PM Warns Against Irregularities in Armed  Forces </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh
Hasina today warned against irregularities in the armed forces,
saying that the armed forces would be kept above any undesirable
interference.
</P>
<P>
Addressing army officers of the 9th infantry division here
today, the prime minister noted that many irregularities had
occurred in the past and actions were taken beyond rules and
regulations.
</P>
<P>
"I can assure you that my government will not allow anything
outside rules and regulations in the armed forces," she said,
adding that the armed forces would be built as a well-organized,
well-trained, efficient and modern force, leaving behind the dirt
of the past.
</P>
<P>
Hasina took power as the prime minister on June 23 after her
Awami League became the largest party in Parliament by winning 146
out of the 300 parliamentary seats against 116 seats bagged by the
ex-ruling Bangladesh Nationalist Party (BNP) in the June 12
general elections.
</P>
<P>
Spelling out the government's aims and objectives, Prime
Minister Hasina disclosed that a guideline, incorporating the
hopes and aspirations of the people, would be given to the armed
forces to uphold the national interests.
</P>
<P>
The Chief of Army Staff, Lt. Gen. Mahbubur Rahman, also spoke
on the occasion.  
</P>
