<HEADLINE> 8 Killed, 26 Wounded in Kabul </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Eight people were killed and 26
others injured today in rocket attacks in the Afghan capital of
Kabul, said reports from the war-torn city.
</P>
<P>
The rockets, fired by the Afghan Taliban religious student
militia, struck the city's southwestern suburbs this morning, just
ahead of the scheduled swearing-in ceremony of the first nine
ministers in the new coalition government.
</P>
<P>
Eight people, including a group of fruit and vegetable vendors
and their customers, were killed on the spot when some rockets
struck the road along which they were peddling their goods,
witnesses were quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The rockets did not strike the area where President Burhanuddin
Rabbani was preparing to oversee the oath-taking ceremony for the
ministers in his new government, officials said.  
