<HEADLINE> Transport Fares Rise in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The public transport fares have
since Thursday risen due to Monday's fuel price increase in some
parts of Uganda.
</P>
<P>
In the capital city Kampala, fares rise by 100 Shillings
(about 0.1 U.S. Dollar) for certain traffic, while in northern
cities like Gulu and Kitgum, the rise is as high as 2,000
Shillings (about 2 Dollars).
</P>
<P>
A visit to the north can cost 9,000 to 10,000 Shillings (nine
to 10 Dollars), according to passengers.
</P>
<P>
The price of petrol has been increased by 130 Shillings to
11,110 Shillings per litre and the price of diesel to 960
Shillings, an increase of 100 Shillings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
