<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hangzhou Lotus Popular Overseas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Hangzhou, a tourist city in east
China's Zhejiang Province, has become the largest lotus
exportation base in the country.
</P>
<P>
Each summer, more than a hundred varieties of the lotus, a
large pink water-lily, are grown in Hangzhou and sent abroad for
exhibitions or for research.
</P>
<P>
Hangzhou's lotus is especially popular in Japan and Hong Kong,
and horticulturists from Singapore, Britain and France have come
to Hangzhou for introducing the flower to their countries.
</P>
<P>
A lotus garden at Guozhuang is the biggest lotus-growing base in
China. The garden occupies about two hectares of land, and has more
than 200 varieties of the flower.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, local florists have grown more than 80 new
varieties of lotus, and have discovered a technique to extend
its lifespan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
