<HEADLINE> Chinese Top Judge Meets Uruguayan Counterpart </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Ren Jianxin, president of the
Chinese Supreme People's Court, met with his Uruguayan counterpart
today, in a hope of increasing the exchanges and cooperation
between the judicial departments of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
After extending a welcome to Marrino Chiarlone, president of
the Uruguayan Supreme Court, Ren said he was satisfied with the
growing exchanges and cooperation between judicial departments of
the two countries, particularly the cooperation between the two
supreme courts, along with the steady and smooth growth of
bilateral relations since the two countries forged diplomatic ties.
</P>
<P>
Ren expressed his belief that the Uruguayan court president's
current China trip would promote the academic exchanges between
the two supreme courts. Ren also briefed the guests on the
economic growth and the building of the legal system in his
country.
</P>
<P>
During their stay in China, the Uruguayan guests, who arrived
here Friday, will also travel to east China's Shandong Province to
acquire the first-hand information about the work concerning
Chinese local courts and civil mediation system, which has proven
effective in resolving disputes among people, thus greatly easing
the pressure of the courts.  
</P>
