<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sotomayor, Burrell Win at Salamanca Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MADRID, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Cuba's world record holder Javier
Sotomayor ignored a nagging knee injury to win the men's high jump
with a 2.30-meter leap at an international athletics meeting in
Salamanca, Spain on Friday.
</P>
<P>
It was a timely return to winning form for the Cuban who has
been out of sorts lately, losing in the Cuban Cup and in
Lausanne, Switzerland, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
American world record holder Leroy Burrell, who failed to
qualify for the Olympics, won the 100 meters in a slow time of
10.10.
</P>
<P>
Olympic champion Allen Johnson of the United States knocked
over four hurdles in the 110 meters hurdles and finished just
behind German Florian Schwarthoff, who won in 13.23 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Jamaica's James Beckford registered the year's best outdoor
mark with a leap of 8.46 meters in the long jump, helped by a
timely gust of wind. 
</P>
</TEXT>
