<HEADLINE> US Ambassador to Pakistan Apologizes for Tight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 6 (Xinhua) -- US Ambassador to Pakistan Thomas
Simons today apologized for the over cautious security
arrangements at a reception here on the US Independence Day
Thursday evening that offended Pakistan's Senate Chairman Wasim
Sajjad.
</P>
<P>
Sajjad, invited by the US embassy as the chief guest, left
without entering the door after his car was stopped twice for
security check at the embassy.
</P>
<P>
"I am sorry for the discomfort at the security arrangements,"
Simons said in a written apology to Sajjad, according to a press
release issued here today by the US Information Service.
</P>
<P>
"I regret the need for the precaution we felt obliged to put in
place of the occasion," he said, noting that "during these days we
have been under a specific threats of violence world over."
</P>
<P>
Two Pakistani federal ministers, who attended the reception,
had to leave their cars outside the embassy and went into the
compound in the cars arranged by the embassy.  
</P>
