<HEADLINE> Iran Welcomes Yeltsin's Re-election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Iran today welcomed the re-election
of Russia's President Boris Yeltsin and expressed the hope that
Moscow would be serious in pursuing an independent foreign policy
free from U.S. pressure.
</P>
<P>
All today's local newspapers carried a message of
congratulation by Iranian President Akbar Hashemi Rafsanjani to
his Russian counterpart.
</P>
<P>
Rafsanjani said: "Your re-election is the confirmation of your
policies by the people who have made a great contribution to the
achievements and experiences of human society."
</P>
<P>
He expressed his hope that Iran-Russian relations expand
further during the new term of Yeltsin's presidency on the basis
of international law and good neighborliness.
</P>
<P>
Today's English-language daily Tehran Times published an
editorial, calling for bolstered regional cooperation, as well as
maintaining regional peace and security.
</P>
<P>
The editorial further reiterated that Moscow can create a
strong bloc with third world countries in order to safeguard the
interests of member states vis-a-vis unilateral decisions taken by
the U.S. in the international arena.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few years, Russia should have learned lessons
from its relations with the U.S., it said, adding that the result
of the runoff showed that almost half of Russia's population is
dissatisfied with the Western impact on Russia.
</P>
<P>
It concluded that continuing the reforms will appease those
who voted for him, while putting a distance from the West,
especially the U.S., will expand his popular base at home and
boost Russia's relations with third world countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
