<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Aidid's Militlamen Advance Into Medina, Mogadishu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, July 6 (Xinhua) -- At least 17 people were killed
and more than 69 others wounded yesterday when the major two
Somali factions were battling over control of the southwestern
Medina district in the capital city Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
Forces loyal to South Mogadishu warlord Mohamed Farah Aidid
have advanced into the district, gaining two square kilometers
from the northern and southern ends of Medina.
</P>
<P>
The district is the largest in Mogadishu with a population of
approximately 200,000, mainly in support of north Mogadishu
strongman Ali Mahdi Mohamed.
</P>
<P>
Both faction leaders have self claimed presidency of the
horn of Africa country.
</P>
<P>
Heavy and small machine guns, 106 mm recoilless rifles, 102 mm
mortars and anti-aircraft missiles were put to use in the
fighting, which still continues.
</P>
<P>
According to eyewitnesses, General Aidid has been holding a
siege on Medina in an effort to persuade its inhabitants to
surrender their weapons, an attempt which has never been realized
during the six-year civil war.
</P>
<P>
Supporters of Ali Mahdi Mohamed in Medina are having
difficulty in getting essential drugs for the wounded since
there's no single official hospital in the neighborhood.
</P>
<P>
More than 170 people are believed to have died and over 400
others wounded in factional fighting since last April. Mogadishu
now seems to be gradually falling into more serious rounds of
warfare. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
