<TEXT>
<P>
Le Figaro - The arrest of the president of National Railway
Company has shaken the company. Loik Le Floch-Prigent, arrested for
suspected abuse of public funds when he was president of
Elf-Aquitaine oil group.
</P>
<P>
- The unemployment rate in the United States lowered to 5.2
percent in June from 5.6 percent in May. However, the good news was
received negatively by the financial markets in the United States.
The Dow Jones index dropped by 114.88 points on Friday.
</P>
