Liberation - A former soldier of the Bosnian Serb army testified
Friday at the International Tribunal on War Crimes in Former
Yugoslavia in the Hague. Drazen Erdemovic, 25, a Croat recruited by
the Serbs, said that his unit killed 1,000 Muslims in Srebrenica in
July 1995.
</P>
<P>
Le Monde - The population in countries of former Soviet Union is
dropping. In Russia, Ukraine, Estonia and Lithuania, each mother
gave birth to 1.7 babies in 1991. But now each mother gives birth to
1.4 babies, a level equal to the mean level of European Union and
lower than those of Scandinavian states, Britain and France.
</P>
<P>
- United Nations officials in New York are worried about the
forthcoming deployment of an international force in Burundi. The
force, made up by African states neighboring Burundi and Rwanda,
consists of troops from Uganda and Zaire, two countries which were
involved in the tribal wars between Tutsis and Hutus in Burundi and
Rwanda. 
