<HEADLINE> Record Output from China's Steel Giant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, July 6 (Xinhua) -- China's biggest steel producer,
the Anshan Steel and Iron Corporation (Angang), turned out a
record 4.28 million tons of steel in the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
Production of rolled steel also set a new record in Angang's
history, reaching 3.18 million tons in the January-June period,
while iron output stood at 4.15 million tons.
</P>
<P>
Angang officials said that the corporation's sales volume
totaled 9.85 billion yuan during the period, with a net profit of
176 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The corporation has handed over 842 million yuan of taxes to
the State so far this year, 191.37 percent more than the same
period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Angang, located in China's northeastern province of Liaoning,
suffered years of losses before 1994. In the last two years the
corporation has strengthened internal management and adapted
itself to market competition, resulting in remarkable economic
returns. 
</P>
