<HEADLINE> Kuwait Says Saudi Security Concerns All Gulf </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Kuwaiti Interior Minister
Sheikh Ali Sabah Al-Salem Al-Sabah has stressed that Saudi
Arabia's security concerns Kuwait and all other gulf countries.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Ali told the local Arabic language daily Al-Watan
(Motherland) in an exclusive interview published here today that
Kuwait strongly refuses any infringement on Saudi Arabia's
security under any condition.
</P>
<P>
"The security of Saudi Arabia is part of the security of Kuwait
and the Gulf as a whole," he said.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks after the recent truck blast at an American
housing complex in Saudi eastern city of Khobar which killed 19
U.S. servicemen and injured nearly 400 others.
</P>
<P>
He condemned the terrorist acts, affirming Kuwait's rejection
of any foreign interference in the internal affairs of gulf states.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait has expressed readiness to cooperate with all countries
to put an end to international terrorism, which he described as
"dangerous and must be confronted with force and firmness," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Security cooperation among the states of the region exists, he
said, stressing that those countries had taken the necessary
measures to fortify their internal fronts so as to "prevent
enemies of the region from penetrating our countries to carry out
whatever they have in mind, namely subversive acts, to undermine
security in the area and spread discords."
</P>
<P>
He indicated without giving names that there were some
countries which were trying to undermine the Gulf security.
</P>
