<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Weekly Report On Kuala Lumpur Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The Kuala Lumpur Stock
Exchange ended the week steadier with second board counters
attracting investors' interest.
</P>
<P>
The composite index dropped 3.13 points this week to 1,133.18
points. However, the all share Emas index rose 0.56 points to
326.02 points from 325.46 points last week, while the industrial
index gained 19.49 points to 2,083.08 from last week's 2,063.59
points.
</P>
<P>
The market opened Monday with players uncertain of its
direction. On Wednesday, the market shed 4.75 points on news of
lower car sales for May and slower monetary aggregate growth for
May.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, the market surged 2.85 points to close at 1,137.92
and turned easier Friday as the much awaited April trade surplus
data were not released.
</P>
<P>
Analysts here said the month could see a wave of selective
bargain hunting by foreign fund managers, while for next week the
market will remain range bound on lack of fresh momentum.
</P>
<P>
Main board turnover this week dropped to 619.516 million shares
valued at 4.549 billion Malaysian ringgit (about 1.819 billion US
dollars) from 689.818 million shares valued at 5.079 billion
ringgit (about 2.03 billion dollars) last week.
</P>
<P>
The second board turnover stood at 279.736 million shares
valued at 2.611 billion ringgit (about 1.04 billion dollars)
compared with 265.22 million shares valued at 2.534 billion
ringgit (about 1.01 billion dollars) previously.
</P>
<P>
Off market deals amounted to 82.78 million shares valued at
782.31 million ringgit (about 312.92 million dollars) from last
week's 82.084 million shares valued at 792.927 million ringgit
(about 317.17 million dollars).  
</P>
</TEXT>
