<HEADLINE> Chinese President Ends Visit to Kazakhstan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
today ended a three-day visit to Kazakhstan and left here for
home, winding up his tour to six European and Central Asian
countries.
</P>
<P>
Kazakh President Nursultan Nazarbayev bade farewell to Jiang at
the State Guest House where Jiang stayed.
</P>
<P>
Jiang arrived here Thursday at the invitation of
Nazarbayev. During his visit, Jiang signed with Nazarbayev a joint
declaration on the relations between Kazakhstan and China, and
witnessed the signing of four cooperation agreements between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
In a message of thanks to the Kazakh president, Jiang said he
had "cordial, friendly and fruitful" talks with Nazarbayev and
other Kazakh leaders during his visit.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president expressed the belief that his visit to
Kazakhstan would open broader prospects for the development of the
good-neighborly ties and mutually-beneficial cooperation between
China and Kazakhstan.
</P>
<P>
Kazakhstan was the last stop of Jiang's six-nation trip that
started on June 23. Earlier he visited Spain, Norway, Romania,
Uzbekistan and Kyrgyzstan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
