<HEADLINE> China Sees Sound Growth in Consumer Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 6 (Xinhua) -- China witnessed a continued sound
growth in sales of consumer goods in May, with national sales
volume up 12 percent in real terms against a year ago.
</P>
<P>
During the month, a total of 189.33 billion yuan worth of
consumer goods were sold, up 19.3 percent in nominal terms from
the same month of last year, according to the Business Information
Center under the Ministry of Internal Trade.
</P>
<P>
The market of residents' daily necessities kept flourishing as
retailers stepped up competition in the summer season.
</P>
<P>
Figures from a chosen group of 80 large department stores showed
that sales of garments increased by 7.2 percent and sales of
shoes climbed 14.2 percent in May.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, sales of household electrical appliances chalked up
an increase of 14.6 percent and sales of detergents jumped by 34.1
percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
