<HEADLINE> Four Burnt to Death in West Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Four persons, including three
children, were burnt to death in an alleged arson crime at a
western Nepali village, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
A house of an ex-policeman at Biskot village of Rukum district,
about 200 kilometers west of Kathmandu, was set ablaze Thursday
evening by unknown criminals, the Kathmandu Post Daily said.
</P>
<P>
House owner Dhanu Jaisi was out of home when the incident
occurred but his wife and three children were killed in the fire,
the paper said.
</P>
<P>
Culprits of the arson were yet to be determined, but police
suspected that it was carried out by an extremist leftist group
which has conducted a series of criminal activities including
armed attack and arson mainly in western Nepal's hilly areas since
last February, according to the paper.
</P>
<P>
More than 20 people had been killed in the ultra-leftist
movement under the name of "people's war."  
</P>
</TEXT>
