<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Security Network in Northern Sri Lanka Tightened </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The bomb explosion set off by a woman suicide bomber belonging
to the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) in the heart of
Jaffna city Thursday left 23 people dead and over 60 wounded.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the attack is a subtle attempt to retard the
governments' rehabilitation plan in the city.
</P>
<P>
But the government is never frightened and the attempt is
doomed to failure, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The sources said a heavily bandaged Housing Minister N.S. De
Silva, who was injured in the explosion, said at the Colombo
National Hospital last night that he saw the brutal act of the
LTTE, but he hoped to go back soon to the north for the
rehabilitation plan on Jaffna Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting against the government for a
separate Tamil state in the north and east of the country since
1983. More than 50,000 people have been killed in the ethnic war.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
