<HEADLINE> Japanese Company to Probe Methane Hydrate in Okhotsk Sea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, July 6 (Xinhua) --- The Japan National Oil Corp. will
start to investigate methane hydrate next week in the Sea of
Okhotsk, said company officials in Sapporo Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The two-week-long investigation will begin next Tuesday with
the help of a Norwegian research ship, the officials added.
</P>
<P>
The oil company, which is under the control of the Ministry of
International Trade and Industry (MITI), will also conduct a
similar probe in August in the Pacific Ocean.
</P>
<P>
Japan is estimated to deposit six trillion cubic meters of
methane hydrate, which is considered to be a potential energy
resource for the future.
</P>
<P>
The probe is a part of the MITI's five-year research plan on
methane hydrate which the ministry launched in 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
