<HEADLINE> Myanmar, Thailand to Explore Gold, Copper, Platinum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar and Thailand will jointly
explore gold, copper and platinum in Myanmar, according to today's
New Light of Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
Under a contract signed here Friday between the Myanmar
Department of Geological Survey and Mineral Exploration and Atina
Time Square Ltd of Thailand, the two parties will carry out the
exploration.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar has been extending invitation to foreign companies for
conducting exploration operations in this country.
</P>
<P>
Foreign companies involved in gold and copper exploration in
Myanmar since 1995 include those from Canada, Singapore,
Australia, the United States and Thailand.  
</P>
