<HEADLINE> Latin American Economic Briefs (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY -- Mexican sugar production of this year will reach
a record high of 4.365 million tons, a 2.6 percent increase over
that of last year.
</P>
<P>
Production to June 15 had reached 4,359,232 tons, 98 percent of
the production foreseen for this year, said a spokesman for the
National Union of Sugar Cane Producers.
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- The well-known French car company, Peugeot de
Francia, will invest 500 million U.S. dollars until the year 2000
in Sevel Argentina, an Argentine car company, said Yves Barbe,
Peugeot de Francia general director, here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Yves Barbe also announced the participation of Sevel Argentina
in the Peugeot projects for the South American Common Market.
</P>
<P>
BRASILIA -- Brazilian exports reached 22.919 billion
U.S. dollars during the first half of this year, a 6.85 percent
increase over that of the same period last year, according to
Mauricio Cortes, secretary of Foreign Trade in the Brazilian
Ministry of Industry, Commerce and Tourism on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- Argentine exports in May rose to a record high
of 2.4 billion U.S. dollars, with a 543 million dollar surplus for
the month.
</P>
<P>
The exports figure represented a 5.6 percent increase over that
of the same period last year, according to the latest report from
the country's Economic Programming Secretariat. 
