<HEADLINE> MERCOSUR to Establish Organ to Solve Economic Conflicts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The South American Common Market
(MERCOSUR) is considering the setting up of an inter-governmental
body within the organization to solve conflicts damaging economic
competence.
</P>
<P>
A Brazilian high-ranking official said here today that the new
body could in principle decide any merger that would have
repercussions on this regional market, which is made up of
Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay.
</P>
<P>
"This organ would complement the existing laws on the matter in
each of the member countries," said Carlo Alberto Simas Magalhaes,
head of the Common Market Division in the Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Brazil is preparing a protocol to defend economic competence
for the regional bloc, according to Simas Magalhaes. 
</P>
