<HEADLINE> Olympic Mascot Attracts Little Attention </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Introduced with much fanfare during
closing ceremony of the Barcelona Olympics four years ago, the
blue buglike mascot of the Atlanta Games attracts little attention
here.
</P>
<P>
Some 26 percent of those surveyed recently said they have seen
him, 72 percent said they haven't, and three percent said they
don't know.
</P>
<P>
Even many Atlantans, who have lived with him for four years,
don't know whatitiz, the mascot's original name which had been
called too strange by many.
</P>
<P>
The good news for the mascot designer is that he's growing on
folks. The people who acknowledge seeing him generally like him.
Nearly 57 percent said he is at least somewhat appealing and 16
percent find him downright delightful.
</P>
<P>
However, the 40 percent said he's not appealing at all. And
three percent refused to express their opinion publicly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
