<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil's Instant Coffee Exports Up, But Income Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's instant coffee export
increased in the first half of the year, but export earnings
slipped, the Brazilian Instant Coffee Industry Association (ABCS)
said today.
</P>
<P>
Some 28,000 tons of instant coffee was exported during the
first half of the year, up 5.4 percent over the same period of
last year.
</P>
<P>
In contrast, export income totaled 207.3 million U.S. dollars,
28 percent less than expected.
</P>
<P>
ABCS blamed the drop on the high price of green coffee, the raw
material for producing instant coffee, in the domestic
market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
