<HEADLINE> China to Use 3.5 Billion Dollars in Chemical Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 6 (Xinhua) -- China expects to use 3.5 billion
US dollars of overseas funds in its chemical industry in the
next five years, official sources said.
</P>
<P>
The industry has to open itself to overseas investors as its
development needs both overseas funds and technology, said Vice
Minister of Chemical Industry He Guoqiang.
</P>
<P>
Overseas chemical producers can participate in the development
of China's chemical industry by applying their advantages in
capital and technology, and open a vast market for themselves, he
said.
</P>
<P>
During the past 17 years, China has used 6.5 billion
U.S. dollars of overseas funds in the chemical industry, with
5,500 joint ventures established.
</P>
<P>
A number of large projects have been completed to help increase
production of chemical fertilizers, rubber products, ethylene,
synthesized materials and fine chemical products.
</P>
<P>
Last year, China's foreign trade in chemical products amounted
to 29.7 billion U.S. dollars, with exports totaling 11.6 billion
U.S. dollars and imports totaling 18.1 billion U.S. dollars.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
