<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The Red Cross Society of China sent
400,000 yuan in emergency aid to flood-stricken provinces of
Guizhou, Anhui and Zhejiang Friday.
</P>
<P>
A task force headed by Sun Baiqiu, the society's deputy
president, has also been dispatched to help organize local
disaster-relief work.
</P>
<P>
