provinces this week, leaving at least 237 dead and 1.3 million
hectares of farmland swamped, according to official figures.
</P>
<P>
The Red Cross Society in Hong Kong has decided to donate
600,000 yuan to those areas, while the Red Cross Society in Taiwan
Province has also decided to provide 200,000 U.S. dollars in
emergency aid.  
