<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Scientists Develop Anti-fire and Anti-theft System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Chinese scientists have developed a
system which can monitor fire and burglary simultaneously in a
building with an area of several hundred square meters.
</P>
<P>
The system, which can automatically distinguish a burning
cigarette butt, and detect the slightest motion of an object in a
room with an area of several hundred sq m, was developed by
professors Fan Weicheng and Wang Qing'an and others at the Chinese
University of Science and Technology in Hefei, capital of east
China's Anhui Province.
</P>
<P>
The system consists of a sub-system for the early probing and
pinpointing of the location of fires, an automatic fire
extinguishing system and a sub-system recording fires and
burglaries. It also has common monitoring functions.
</P>
<P>
Electronic information and integration technology is used as
the 'brains' of the system. 
</P>
</TEXT>
