<HEADLINE> Russia to Cope With Budget Problem: Chernomyrdin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Russian Prime Minister Viktor
Chernomyrdin said today that 75 trillion rubles in tax revenues
(15 billion U.S. dollars) failed to be collected into federal or
regional budget coffers over the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a cabinet meeting, the prime minister said that
fighting tax evasion and exerting a tighter control on cash flows
will be the basic task of the new government, aimed at alleviating
budgetary and fiscal shortfalls.
</P>
<P>
He said that the 75 trillion rubles could have been used to
better the lives of the Russian people.
</P>
<P>
The Izvestia newspaper reported today that Russia has been
experiencing a budgetary crisis for the past several months.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper warned that the crisis is expected to last until
the end of this year. 
