<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Enterprise Groups Play Important Role in Inner Mongolia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, July 6 (Xinhua) -- North China's Inner Mongolia
Autonomous Region has set up 93 enterprise groups to boost local
economic growth.
</P>
<P>
An official with the regional government said the move was
aimed at vitalizing the state-owned enterprises and changing the
mode of economic growth in the region.
</P>
<P>
In the region's textile and light industrial sector, nine
enterprise groups have been set up by mergers, issuing shares and
other forms.
</P>
<P>
The Ordos Woolens Group, consisting of 33 enterprises, has
expanded its business to other fields such as manufacturing of
electronics and medicine, and commerce and trade. The group
turned in 200 million yuan to the State in profits and taxes in
1995, ranking sixth in the nation's top 100 textile enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Economists said the establishment of enterprise groups helped
to concentrate capital, upgrade the existing enterprises and raise
production efficiency. 
</P>
</TEXT>
