<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xihu Lake Becomes Cleaner, More Beautiful </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, July 6 (Xinhua) -- China's famous tourism spot, Xihu
Lake (the West Lake), has become cleaner and more beautiful with
the removal of more than 30 nearby factories.
</P>
<P>
The factories were threats to the lake in this scenic city
since they produced noise and serious pollution.
</P>
<P>
Since 1993, the Xihu district government has allocated 50
million yuan for the construction of an industrial zone in a spot
far from the lake, to accommodate the displaced factories.
</P>
<P>
The old factories, including a water pump plant, electrical
plant and a paint spraying plant, have been used as kindergartens,
schools and dining halls.
</P>
<P>
Afforestation in nearby areas has also been speeded up in
tandem with the removal of factories.
</P>
<P>
Xihu Lake is located in Hangzhou City, east China's Zhejiang
Province. The lake's water area is 5.2 square kilometers, with a
circumference of 15 kilometers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
