<HEADLINE> Bicycle Exports Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Exports of the China-made
"Phoenix" bicycle hit a historic high of 720,000 during the first
half of this year, up 32 percent from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Phoenix Bicycle Co. Ltd. took in 30.1 million US
dollars from the exports.
</P>
<P>
Phoenix bicycles are hot items in Europe, the United States,
Africa and countries in southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
To cater to foreign consumers, the Phoenix manufacturer has
developed over 20 new models so far this year, and increased the
number of overseas sales outlets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
