<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chirac Visits Saudi Arabia Saturday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 5 (Xinhua) - French president Jacques Chirac will
leave for Saudi Arabia on Saturday on a one-day visit of
"friendship and respect" with a political nature.
</P>
<P>
The visit, the first by the president to the Gulf region, is
made 11 days after a terrorist attack on a U.S. air base in
Dhahran, Saudi Arabia, which killed 19 American soldiers.
</P>
<P>
The French presidential spokeswoman Catherine Colona said that
the visit is made with the background that the president has
called for a more aggressive and ambitious foreign policy in the
Arab world.
</P>
<P>
She said that Saudi Arabia is France's major partner not only
because of its geographical position, but also because of its
influence in the Muslim-Arab world and the role it plays on the
regional "chessboard".
</P>
<P>
The spokeswoman said the Arab policy France is adopting
consists of four principles - dialogues of partnership on an equal
stand, support to Arab people in their rights of
self-determination, support to the aspiration of the Arab people
for solidarity and unity, and support to policies of openness and
peace in Arab states.
</P>
<P>
Accompanying Chirac are Defense Minister Charles Millon,
Foreign Minister Herve de Charette, Interior Minister Jean-Louis
Debre, Industry Minister Franck Borotra, the president of the Arab
Institute in Paris Camille Cabana, and the chairman of
France-Saudi Arabia Friendship Group in the French National
Assembly Olivier Dassault.
</P>
<P>
As in all his trips abroad, Chirac does not invite enterprise
leaders to accompany him.
</P>
<P>
After visiting Saudi Arabia, Chirac will go to Qatar on Sunday
for an official visit.
</P>
<P>
France is a major arms supplier to both Saudi Arabia and Qatar.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
