<DOCNO> XIE19960706.0225 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French Woman to Work on Russian Space Station </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 5 (Xinhua) - Claudie Andre-Deshays, a 39-year-old
rheumatologist, will become the first French women to work in
space.
</P>
<P>
Andre-Deshays will join the mission Cassiopee planned for
August 14-30, which will bring her to the Russian space station
"Mir". In the station, she will set up her lab for experiments on
salamanders, the tailed newtlike amphibian of the order Urodela.
</P>
<P>
Anne-Marie Duprat, head of the Fertile Experiment of Study on
Reproduction in Microgravity for which Andre-Deshays works, said
that Deshays has learned all technologies in physiology for
salamanders.
</P>
<P>
The group's study is based on six female salamenders that have
been fertilized for three years. Deshays will bring them to the
Mir station, inject hormone in them to make them lay eggs and in
the meantime observe the growth of the salamanders' embryos in
micro-gravity in the 14 days she stays 350 kilometers above earth.
</P>
<P>
"We hope to discover if gravity affects or not the way
salamanders grow and how their nerve tube, nerve system and organs
grow, as well as if the little salamanders will come out of their
eggs when returned to earth," said Duprat.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the biological experiments, Deshays will also join
experiments on effects of micro-gravity on human body, including
those on how human being controls its movement in space and why it
is difficult for man to make gestures in space.
</P>
<P>
Two French-designed labs - Physiolab and Cognilab - will be
installed in the "Mir" to help the experiments on brain functions,
cognitive functions, tele-robot technology, neurology, and
occupational therapy for astronauts.
</P>
<P>
Joining the experiments are France's National Center of
Scientific Research, Russia's Institute of Biological Medical
Problems, Russia's Institution of Problems of Information
Transmission, and the space company RKK Energuia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
