<HEADLINE> OAU Council of Ministers Meeting Drags On </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The Organization of African Unity
(OAU) Council of Ministers meeting failed to conclude today as
scheduled owing to the overwhelming documents to be reviewed and
passed.
</P>
<P>
The planned two-day meeting will be resumed on Saturday
starting from 18:00 p.m., according to the OAU Secretariat which
organized the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Ministers from the continent have to review a total of 35
items of agenda ranging from regional peace and stability,
economic integration to a pile of social issues including AIDS,
drug abuse and trafficking, illiteracy, etc.
</P>
<P>
Delegates to the closed-door meeting said "there were simply
no quarrels" during the sessions, even on hot issues such as the
controversial Rwandan refugees problem. 
</P>
</TEXT>
