<DOCNO> XIE19960706.0233 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dar Fair To Apply for UFI Membership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The Dar es Salaam
International Trade Fair (DITF) will lodge formal application to
the Union of International Trade Fairs (UFI) in August this year.
</P>
<P>
This was said by Mbarouk Mwandoro, Director General of the
Board of External Trade (BET) under the Ministry of Trade and
Industries today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a press conference at the on-going 20th DITF here,
Mwandoro said after 20 years of running trade fairs, his
organization is confident of getting the UFI membership.
</P>
<P>
The BET boss said the UFI membership demanded a number of
things be fulfilled by the applicants, including good and
adequate infrastructure and commercial facilities, good
management and a good number of foreign participants.
</P>
<P>
"As a rule the number of participants from overseas should not
be less than 20 percent," Mwandoro told reporters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
